27/src/test/java/com_jcraft/jsch/KeyExchangeTest.java` to exercise `KeyExchange.getFingerPrint()` through the normal `Session.connect(...)` flow instead of a direct test subclass.\n\nWhat changed:\n- Added a bounded in-process mini SSH server that performs a real `diffie-hellman-group1-sha1` key exchange far enough for `Session.checkHost(...)` to run.\n- Generates a valid RSA host key signature so `DHG1.next(...)` succeeds and reaches `KeyExchange.getFingerPrint()`.\n- Verifies the client reaches `SSH_MSG_NEWKEYS`, which happens only after host key checking and fingerprint calculation.\n- Keeps the test focused on `com.jcraft.jsch.KeyExchange`.\n- No reachability metadata or native-image config files were modified.\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per workflow instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0484654c4db2b2fb016a11134a249881a2a3cf3a56e1c378f7\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 832, "output": 948, "cacheRead": 50176, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51956, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779503881203, "responseId": "resp_0484654c4db2b2fb016a11130a41a481a291d89a99858224af"}, "toolResults": []}
